# Build-context guard for the agent image. The context is this playground dir (not the repo
# root), and the Dockerfile copies only specific paths (.coordinate-src, entrypoint.sh, .claude).
# These exclusions make the no-bias / no-secret guarantees explicit and robust against a future
# stray file or a broad `COPY`.

# No-bias: the repo's own agent-guidance files must never be baked into a playground image — a
# CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md anywhere in the context would auto-load and prime the agent.
# See ARCHITECTURE.md § Design principle: no bias.
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
**/CLAUDE.md
**/AGENTS.md

# No-secret: the OAuth token reaches the container via compose env at runtime, never an image
# layer. Keep .env* out of the image build context.
.env
.env.*
